purpose:
(Clinical Focus: This set of values contains codes for laboratory test names associated with microscopic observation method of specimens by gram stain from genitalia, urethra or cervix and the result value is nominal (i.e., organism names).),(Data Element Scope: Laboratory tests names that were ordered or observed.),(Inclusion Criteria: microscopic observation gram stain (cervix, genital, vaginal, penis, semen, or urethra);  

LOINC search:  'microscopic observation gram stain (genital or cervix or vaginal or penis or semen or urethra) -narrative -wet -KOH -cyto'),(Exclusion Criteria: Specimen types that are not (genital, cervix, vaginal, penis, semen, urethra and unspecified specimen types);  
Tests for: Wet prep or KOH (used to ID fungus), and cyto stains (for pap smears))
